{"id":"6097dc09616669001c878d5a","title":"Pure ESM package","image":"https://gyazo.com/1dc1d086bcfc0a2173eedcefeb3a7ff5/raw","created":1620565002,"updated":1620565391,"lines":[{"id":"6097dc09616669001c878d5a","text":"Pure ESM package","created":1620565002,"updated":1620565002},{"id":"6097dc0a4ade4d00002b76f7","text":"[Pure ESM package https://gist.github.com/sindresorhus/a39789f98801d908bbc7ff3ecc99d99c#how-can-i-move-my-commonjs-project-to-esm]","created":1620565002,"updated":1620565002},{"id":"6097dc0a4ade4d00002b76f8","text":"[https://gyazo.com/1dc1d086bcfc0a2173eedcefeb3a7ff5]","created":1620565002,"updated":1620565012},{"id":"6097dc144ade4d00002b76fd","text":">Add \"type\": \"module\" to your package.json.","created":1620565012,"updated":1620565021},{"id":"6097dc1c4ade4d00002b76fe","text":"> Replace \"main\": \"index.js\" with \"exports\": \"./index.js\" in your package.json.","created":1620565021,"updated":1620565021},{"id":"6097dc1c4ade4d00002b76ff","text":"> Update the \"engines\" field in package.json to Node.js 12: \"node\": \">=12.20\".","created":1620565021,"updated":1620565021},{"id":"6097dc1c4ade4d00002b7700","text":"> Remove 'use strict'; from all JavaScript files.","created":1620565021,"updated":1620565021},{"id":"6097dc1c4ade4d00002b7701","text":"> Replace all require()/module.export with import/export.","created":1620565021,"updated":1620565021},{"id":"6097dc1c4ade4d00002b7702","text":"> Use only full relative file paths for imports: import x from '.'; → import x from './index.js';.","created":1620565021,"updated":1620565021},{"id":"6097dc1c4ade4d00002b7703","text":"> If you have a TypeScript type definition (for example, index.d.ts), update it to use ESM imports/exports.","created":1620565021,"updated":1620565021},{"id":"6097dc1c4ade4d00002b7704","text":"> Optional but recommended, use the node: protocol for imports.","created":1620565021,"updated":1620565021},{"id":"6097dc0a4ade4d00002b76f9","text":"","created":1620565002,"updated":1620565002},{"